What does the word 'polymorphism' mean?

  Many forms

What does it mean when we apply polymorphism to OO design? Give a simple Java example.

  A class is created as if it were another class - using an abstract class to extend another one.

What can we use to implement polymorphism in Java?

  Interfaces, Abstract Classes, Inheritance

How many 'forms' can an object take when using polymorphism?

  No limit

Give an example of when you could use polymorphism.

  When you need several classes which all share similar parameters - room - conference rooms - bed rooms

Composition and Aggregation
What do we mean by 'composition' in reference to object-oriented programming?

  When an object contains other objects

When would you use composition? Provide a simple example in Java.

  Classes can use behaviour from other objects

Give a difference between composition and aggregation?

  With composition, an object owns behaviour from other objects. with aggregation, objects use behaviour from other classes

What is/are the advantage(s) of using composition/aggregation?

  you wont have to rely on an inheritence tree with composition

When using composition, when an object is destroyed, what happens to all the objects it is composed of?

  they are destroyed

When using aggregation, when an object is destroyed, what happens to all the objects it is composed of?

  They still exist
